snippet.textDisplay: The only other time you see Nat torn apart like this is the aftermath of Infinity War. That's how we know that Thanos really was a threat that Nat truly feared. You can see the same terror in her eyes on 1:36. This is how you know that Taskmaster is going to break Nat. Notice before Infinity War, it was difficult to make Nat terrified, even during the Age of Ultron. However, I think the fight with Taskmaster is going to hurt her hard, and he could be her breaking point. This is why I am so psyched for Taskmaster. It seems like he is going to truly damage/affect one of our beloved heroes. Taskmaster is gonna be a beast in this movie and I can't wait. I think he is going to take down her family one...by one...until he gets to her.

snippet.textDisplay: What Marvel hides about the fight scenes is that the actors participate minimally in them. The little they record is shown in the making ofs, making the audience believe that they do the fights. The high kicks, stunts are done by stunt doubles. To disguise this, the stunt-double has its back to the camera, its face covered by hair or by a mask. When this is not possible, the face is digitally replaced by the actor's face.
